# Force LF on the committed, generated documentation so the cross-platform
# drift-check tests (rules_json / variant_pages_doc / variants_doc) compare the
# freshly-rendered LF output byte-for-byte against the checked-out files on
# Windows too. Without this, git's autocrlf checks these out with CRLF and the
# `assert_eq!` diffs on line endings. The tests also normalize CRLF defensively.
docs/** text eol=lf
